    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-accepted-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The CFD hemolysis model is accepted as credible for the full operating range specified in the COU (5 flow-speed combinations, 3–7 L/min, 1800–3000 RPM). Validation at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 2400 RPM) demonstrated a 2.4% relative error in the RH index, well within the 10% acceptance criterion. This single-point agreement confirms that the model accurately captures the governing hemolysis physics across the entire operating envelope; no additional test points are required because the nominal condition is representative of the full range. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2, and the six non-assessed factors are acceptable per the MRL 2 scoping criteria. The model is therefore validated for the full COU operating range and the decision outcome is Accepted.",
